sys_hub_flow.description:
Parallel subflow to retrieve range of material data from the SAP S4/HANA RFC system.

Inputs:

  • Service Record - This input is an integration service job tracker record that contains the details about the executed service or job.
  • Connection Name - This input is a Connection and Credential alias record used to connect to the target system.
  • ERP Source - Input to determine the target system.
  • Row Count - Number of rows to be retrieved from the SAP system.
  • Range -  Specifies the range of records that will be retrieved from SAP system.
  • Service properties - JSON payload containing the integration service properties.

Outputs:

  • Status - Will be set to "1", if the request is "Success" or will be set to "2", if the request is "Error”.
  • Error - Reason for error. Populated only when an error occurs.

To use this subflow, the corresponding SAP S4/HANA RFC connection and credential must be created and associated with the SAP S4/HANA Connection & Credential alias. Learn More

Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More.

sys_hub_flow_snapshot.description:
Parallel subflow to retrieve range of material data from the SAP S4/HANA RFC system.

Inputs:

  • Service Record - This input is an integration service job tracker record that contains the details about the executed service or job.
  • Connection Name - This input is a Connection and Credential alias record used to connect to the target system.
  • ERP Source - Input to determine the target system.
  • Row Count - Number of rows to be retrieved from the SAP system.
  • Range -  Specifies the range of records that will be retrieved from SAP system.
  • Service properties - JSON payload containing the integration service properties.

Outputs:

  • Status - Will be set to "1", if the request is "Success" or will be set to "2", if the request is "Error”.
  • Error - Reason for error. Populated only when an error occurs.

To use this subflow, the corresponding SAP S4/HANA RFC connection and credential must be created and associated with the SAP S4/HANA Connection & Credential alias. Learn More

Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More.
